OL,3,CWho's out? The biggest losers in
OL,4,CJersey's election
OL,6,FMr Le Fondre entered the States
OL,7,FAssembly in 2005 as the Deputy of St
OL,8,FLawrence. He held this position for 13
OL,9,Fyears, before being elected as a
OL,10,FSenator in 2018, and subsequently
OL,11,FChief Minister.
OL,13,FHe served in this role through the
OL,14,FCOVID pandemic, Brexit and the start
OL,15,Fof the ongoing Ukraine war. He went on
OL,16,Fto lose his seat in 2022 election and
OL,17,Fwas attempting to return to the States
OL,18,FAssembly.
OL,26,@nD@Lrr
